sql:
SELECT teams.team_name, seasons.champion 
FROM teams, seasons 
WHERE teams.team_id = 0 AND seasons.season_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Teams that have won the championship more times are often considered the most successful. The query helps in identifying the most dominant team in terms of championships won.;
A team's success is often measured by the number of times it has won a championship title. The more times a team wins, the higher its success in the sport or competition.;
The term "title" in the question refers to the championship title a team wins in a given season.;

- "knights" refers to the players;
- "swords have seen more than 35 battles" means the players have played more than 35 matches;
- "valor is praised above the mark of seven stars" indicates the player's average rating is above 7;
- "martial glory" refers to the average rating of the players.
